<system>
You are an expert reviewer evaluating hierarchical decompositions of benchmark problems. You output ONLY a single JSON object: {"verdict": "acceptable" | "needs revision", "justification": "<one to two sentences>"}.

A decomposition is "acceptable" if:
- "global" captures the overall plan in one sentence,
- the union of subtasks covers what the problem actually asks for,
- atomics under each subtask are operational steps that, executed in order, would complete that subtask,
- "global_atomics" contains only steps that genuinely cross subtasks (verification, final checks, etc.),
- gold_actions mirrors the same structure with specific resolved actions.

It "needs revision" if any of the above fail clearly.

Output ONLY the JSON object, with no prose before or after, no markdown fencing.

</system>

Benchmark: WorkArena++
Domain: web agent / Airlines (Mind2Web proxy — WorkArena++ unavailable on HF)

Problem (truncated to 1500 chars):
Compare all membership tier benefits.

Candidate v2 hierarchy:
{
  "global": "Navigate an airline's loyalty program website, identify all membership tiers, extract benefits for each tier, and produce a structured comparison table.",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "subtask": "Locate and navigate to the airline loyalty program page",
      "atomics": [
        "Load the airline's homepage",
        "Find and click the loyalty/membership program link in header or navigation",
        "Wait for membership overview page to load"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Identify all membership tiers in the program",
      "atomics": [
        "Scan the membership overview page for tier names and levels",
        "Note the tier hierarchy (e.g., Member → Silver → Gold → Platinum)",
        "Record all tier identifiers and their position in the hierarchy"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Extract benefits for each membership tier",
      "atomics": [
        "Access the first tier's benefit details via navigation or comparison view",
        "Scrape all listed benefits (points earning, baggage allowance, seat upgrades, lounge access, priority boarding)",
        "Repeat extraction for each remaining tier",
        "Consolidate all benefits with tier mappings"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Structure and organize the benefit comparison",
      "atomics": [
        "Group benefits by category (Earning, Perks, Baggage, Lounge Access)",
        "Create comparison matrix with tiers as columns and benefits as rows",
        "Mark tier-exclusive or standout benefits",
        "Format comparison as markdown table or JSON structure"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "global_atomics": [
    "Cross-check that all identified tiers appear in the final comparison",
    "Verify no benefits from the website were omitted from the comparison"
  ]
}

Candidate v2 gold_actions:
{
  "global": "Navigate airline loyalty program, enumerate all membership tiers, extract per-tier benefits via detail pages or comparison view, and produce a row-by-benefit, column-by-tier comparison matrix.",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "subtask": "Navigate to airline loyalty program overview page",
      "atomics": [
        "Load airline homepage and click Loyalty/Membership header link",
        "Wait for tier overview page to render",
        "Confirm tier names and summary benefits are visible"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Parse tier names and record membership tier hierarchy",
      "atomics": [
        "Extract tier names from page DOM (Member, Silver, Gold, Platinum, etc.)",
        "Document tier progression order from lowest to highest",
        "Count total number of distinct tiers"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Scrape benefit details for each tier from detail pages or comparison table",
      "atomics": [
        "Navigate to first tier detail page or open tier comparison view",
        "Extract benefit values (points multiplier, baggage pieces, lounge passes, boarding priority)",
        "Advance to next tier and repeat benefit extraction",
        "Map each benefit to its corresponding tier"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Assemble benefit comparison matrix and format output",
      "atomics": [
        "Create column headers with each tier name",
        "Create rows for each unique benefit type",
        "Populate cells with benefit values or Yes/No indicators",
        "Export as markdown table or JSON object"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "global_atomics": []
}

Output the JSON verdict now.

